<Layout title="Surgical Treatments" description="Guide to surgical fertility treatments including laparoscopy, hysteroscopy, and procedures for endometriosis, fibroids, and blocked fallopian tubes.">
	<section class="hero-mini">
		<div class="container">
			<nav class="breadcrumb">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<a href="/treatments/">Treatments</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<span>Surgical Treatments</span>
			</nav>
			<h1>Surgical Fertility Treatments</h1>
			<p>Procedures to diagnose and correct structural issues affecting fertility.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="intro-box">
				<h2>Overview</h2>
				<p>Surgical treatments address physical abnormalities that may prevent conception or successful pregnancy. These procedures can be diagnostic (to identify problems) or therapeutic (to fix them), and often both.</p>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Laparoscopy</h2>

			<div class="procedure-card">
				<div class="procedure-header">
					<div class="procedure-icon">üî¨</div>
					<div class="procedure-info">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>Minimally invasive surgery using a thin camera (laparoscope) inserted through small incisions in the abdomen to view and treat pelvic organs.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="used-for">
					<h4>Used For</h4>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Endometriosis</strong>
							<span>Removal of endometrial implants and scar tissue</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Ovarian cysts</strong>
							<span>Removal while preserving ovarian tissue</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Fallopian tubes</strong>
							<span>Assess patency, remove hydrosalpinx</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Fibroids</strong>
							<span>Removal of subserosal or intramural fibroids</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Ectopic pregnancy</strong>
							<span>Treatment of tubal pregnancy</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Unexplained infertility</strong>
							<span>Diagnostic exploration</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="procedure-details">
					<h4>Procedure Details</h4>
					<div class="details-grid">
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">üíâ</span>
							<span class="text">General anesthesia</span>
						</div>
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">‚úÇÔ∏è</span>
							<span class="text">2-4 small incisions (5-12mm)</span>
						</div>
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">üè†</span>
							<span class="text">Outpatient; go home same day</span>
						</div>
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">üîÑ</span>
							<span class="text">Recovery: 1-2 weeks</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="costs-section">
					<h4>Costs</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Diagnostic laparoscopy</span>
							<span class="price">$5,000-$10,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Operative laparoscopy (treatment)</span>
							<span class="price">$10,000-$25,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="insurance-note">Insurance often covers diagnostic and medically necessary procedures.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Hysteroscopy</h2>

			<div class="procedure-card">
				<div class="procedure-header">
					<div class="procedure-icon">üîç</div>
					<div class="procedure-info">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>A thin camera inserted through the cervix into the uterus to view and treat problems inside the uterine cavity.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="used-for">
					<h4>Used For</h4>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Uterine polyps</strong>
							<span>Removal of endometrial polyps</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Submucosal fibroids</strong>
							<span>Fibroids protruding into uterine cavity</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Uterine septum</strong>
							<span>Division and removal of the septum</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Asherman's syndrome</strong>
							<span>Removal of intrauterine adhesions/scar tissue</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Retained tissue</strong>
							<span>After miscarriage or D&C</span>
						</div>
						<div class="use-item">
							<strong>Abnormal bleeding</strong>
							<span>Diagnosis and treatment</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="procedure-details">
					<h4>Procedure Details</h4>
					<div class="details-grid">
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">üíâ</span>
							<span class="text">Local, sedation, or general anesthesia</span>
						</div>
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">‚úì</span>
							<span class="text">No incisions (through cervix)</span>
						</div>
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">üè†</span>
							<span class="text">Outpatient procedure</span>
						</div>
						<div class="detail-item">
							<span class="icon">üîÑ</span>
							<span class="text">Recovery: 1-2 days</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="costs-section">
					<h4>Costs</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Diagnostic hysteroscopy</span>
							<span class="price">$1,500-$5,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Operative hysteroscopy</span>
							<span class="price">$5,000-$15,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Myomectomy</h2>

			<div class="procedure-card">
				<div class="procedure-header">
					<div class="procedure-icon">ü©∫</div>
					<div class="procedure-info">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>Surgical removal of uterine fibroids while preserving the uterus.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="types-section">
					<h4>Types</h4>
					<div class="types-grid">
						<div class="type-card">
							<div class="type-badge best">Least Invasive</div>
							<h5>Hysteroscopic</h5>
							<p>For fibroids inside the cavity</p>
						</div>
						<div class="type-card">
							<h5>Laparoscopic</h5>
							<p>For fibroids on outside or in wall</p>
						</div>
						<div class="type-card">
							<h5>Robotic-assisted</h5>
							<p>Laparoscopic with robotic precision</p>
						</div>
						<div class="type-card">
							<h5>Abdominal (open)</h5>
							<p>For large or numerous fibroids</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="when-helps">
					<h4>When It Helps Fertility</h4>
					<div class="helps-grid">
						<div class="help-item benefit">
							<span class="indicator">‚úì</span>
							<div class="content">
								<strong>Submucosal fibroids</strong>
								<span>Inside cavity - clear benefit</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="help-item moderate">
							<span class="indicator">~</span>
							<div class="content">
								<strong>Large intramural fibroids</strong>
								<span>In wall - may help</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="help-item unlikely">
							<span class="indicator">‚úó</span>
							<div class="content">
								<strong>Subserosal fibroids</strong>
								<span>On outside - unlikely to affect fertility</span>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="recovery-section">
					<h4>Recovery</h4>
					<div class="recovery-grid">
						<div class="recovery-item">
							<span class="type">Hysteroscopic</span>
							<span class="time">1-2 days</span>
						</div>
						<div class="recovery-item">
							<span class="type">Laparoscopic</span>
							<span class="time">1-2 weeks</span>
						</div>
						<div class="recovery-item">
							<span class="type">Abdominal</span>
							<span class="time">4-6 weeks</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="recovery-note">Wait 3-6 months before attempting pregnancy</p>
				</div>

				<div class="costs-section">
					<h4>Costs</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Hysteroscopic myomectomy</span>
							<span class="price">$5,000-$12,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Laparoscopic myomectomy</span>
							<span class="price">$10,000-$25,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Abdominal myomectomy</span>
							<span class="price">$15,000-$30,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Tubal Surgery</h2>

			<div class="procedure-card">
				<div class="tubal-procedures">
					<div class="tubal-procedure">
						<h4>Tubal Ligation Reversal</h4>
						<p>Reconnecting fallopian tubes after sterilization.</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Success depends on type of original ligation and remaining tube length</li>
							<li><span class="stat">40-80%</span> pregnancy rates if tubes can be reconnected</li>
							<li>Alternative: IVF (bypasses tubes entirely)</li>
							<li>Cost: <span class="price">$6,000-$15,000</span> (rarely covered by insurance)</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="tubal-procedure">
						<h4>Salpingostomy/Fimbrioplasty</h4>
						<p>Opening blocked fallopian tubes or repairing the fimbriae (finger-like projections).</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Limited success rates (<span class="stat">20-30%</span>)</li>
							<li>Increased ectopic pregnancy risk</li>
							<li>IVF often preferred over tubal repair</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="tubal-procedure">
						<h4>Salpingectomy</h4>
						<p>Removal of damaged fallopian tubes, often recommended before IVF.</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Hydrosalpinx (fluid-filled tube) can reduce IVF success</li>
							<li>Removing damaged tubes improves IVF outcomes by <span class="stat">50%</span></li>
							<li>Required for ectopic pregnancy treatment in some cases</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Male Fertility Surgery</h2>

			<div class="procedure-card">
				<div class="male-procedures">
					<div class="male-procedure">
						<h4>Varicocele Repair</h4>
						<p>Correction of enlarged veins in the scrotum.</p>
						<div class="procedure-stats">
							<div class="stat-item">
								<span class="value">40%</span>
								<span class="label">of infertile men have varicoceles</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<ul>
							<li>May improve sperm count and motility</li>
							<li>Options: Microsurgical, laparoscopic, or embolization</li>
							<li>Cost: <span class="price">$5,000-$15,000</span></li>
							<li>Results seen 3-6 months after surgery</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="male-procedure">
						<h4>Vasectomy Reversal</h4>
						<p>Reconnecting the vas deferens after vasectomy.</p>
						<div class="success-by-time">
							<div class="time-item">
								<span class="time">&lt;10 years</span>
								<span class="rate good">75-95%</span>
								<span class="label">sperm return</span>
							</div>
							<div class="time-item">
								<span class="time">&gt;15 years</span>
								<span class="rate moderate">30-70%</span>
								<span class="label">sperm return</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<ul>
							<li>Pregnancy rates: 30-75%</li>
							<li>Cost: <span class="price">$5,000-$15,000</span></li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="male-procedure">
						<h4>Sperm Retrieval Procedures</h4>
						<p>For men with azoospermia (no sperm in ejaculate):</p>
						<div class="retrieval-types">
							<div class="retrieval-item">
								<strong>TESA</strong>
								<span>Testicular sperm aspiration (needle biopsy)</span>
							</div>
							<div class="retrieval-item">
								<strong>TESE</strong>
								<span>Testicular sperm extraction (surgical biopsy)</span>
							</div>
							<div class="retrieval-item">
								<strong>Micro-TESE</strong>
								<span>Microscope-assisted extraction</span>
							</div>
							<div class="retrieval-item">
								<strong>MESA</strong>
								<span>Microsurgical epididymal sperm aspiration</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<p class="cost-note">Cost: <span class="price">$3,000-$15,000</span> | Sperm used with ICSI during IVF</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">When Surgery vs. IVF?</h2>

			<div class="comparison-table">
				<div class="table-container">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Consider Surgery When</th>
								<th>Consider IVF When</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							<tr>
								<td>Young age (&lt;35)</td>
								<td>Advanced age (&gt;38)</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Single correctable issue</td>
								<td>Multiple fertility factors</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Good ovarian reserve</td>
								<td>Diminished ovarian reserve</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Want multiple children over time</td>
								<td>Limited time to conceive</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Prefer to try natural conception</td>
								<td>Need genetic testing</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Surgery likely to fully resolve issue</td>
								<td>Severe damage unlikely to be repaired</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="callout-box info">
				<div class="callout-icon">üí°</div>
				<div class="callout-content">
					<h4>Combined Approach</h4>
					<p>Sometimes surgery is recommended before IVF - for example, removing a hydrosalpinx or large fibroids to improve IVF success rates.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Finding a Surgeon</h2>

			<div class="tips-grid">
				<div class="tip-item">
					<span class="icon">üéì</span>
					<p>Look for fellowship-trained reproductive endocrinologists or reproductive surgeons</p>
				</div>
				<div class="tip-item">
					<span class="icon">üìä</span>
					<p>Ask about their experience with your specific condition</p>
				</div>
				<div class="tip-item">
					<span class="icon">üî¨</span>
					<p>Inquire about minimally invasive techniques</p>
				</div>
				<div class="tip-item">
					<span class="icon">‚ùì</span>
					<p>Understand the expected impact on your fertility</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<nav class="nav-footer">
				<a href="/treatments/preservation/" class="nav-prev">
					<span class="nav-label">Previous</span>
					<span class="nav-title">‚Üê Fertility Preservation</span>
				</a>
				<a href="/treatments/recurrent-loss/" class="nav-next">
					<span class="nav-label">Next</span>
					<span class="nav-title">Recurrent Loss ‚Üí</span>
				</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

